Steps:
1. Create an E2-Medium Instance:
gcloud compute instances create INSTANCE_NAME \
 --machine-type=e2-medium \
 --image-family=debian-11 \
 --image-project=debian-cloud \
 --boot-disk-size=10GB \
 --zone=asia-south2-a \
 --tags=http-server \



2. sudo apt-get update


3. sudo apt-get install apache2



4. sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf



5. Add the path of your webApp, your ip. It should be looking like this ðŸ‘‡ 
<VirtualHost your-IP:80>
 ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
 DocumentRoot /home/user/WebApp-name

 ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/error.log
 CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/access.log combined

 <Directory /home/user/WebApp-name>
 AllowOverride All
 </Directory>
</VirtualHost>


6. sudo service apache2 restart


7. Open a new tab and paste this into the URL tab: your-ip:80



Note âš  : Don't forget to add your WebApp folder in the VM. I have done this using Cloud Shell. you can use this or clone your file using the git clone command.

